	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />CGA actually supports a surprising number of not-very-usefully different palettes:<br />- red, green, brown<br />- darker cyan, darker magenta, grey<br />- bright dilute red, bright dilute green, bright yellow<br />- bright cyan, bright magenta, bright white (the one you've demonstrated here)<br />- red, cyan, white<br />- bright dilute red, bright cyan, bright white<br /><br />plus, you can change the 4th color to any one of the 16 intrinsics (not just black, as you have here).<br /><br />(q.v. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_8-bit_computer_hardware_palettes#CGA" class="postlink">Wikipedia</a>)<br /><br />This is entirely ignoring <a href="http://www.reenigne.org/misc/cga_composite.png" class="postlink">artifact colors</a> over the CGA's composite output.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


